  "riddle": "1. In a village nestled among the hills of Slovenia, a page reveals its height above the sea. What is this elevation, in meters?\n\n2. Follow the trail of the winding waterway that shares its name with a unique flower. What distance does this river flow, measured in kilometers?\n\n3. Seek out the geography of the mentioned river — how far above the earth does the liquid flow through this mountainous landscape?\n\n4. Nearby, nature has painted a scene filled with lush greenery — count the parks that flank this river's banks.\n\n5. Combine the height of the flowing waters from clue 3 with the number of recreational spots discovered in clue 4. What do you find?\n\n6. Now, veer over to the banks of a significant river in South Carolina, known for its role in the American Revolution. Discover how many souls call the country of Slovenia their home.\n\n7. Now, in a twist of fate, reverse the digits of the population you just uncovered in clue 6. What new number emerges?\n\n8. Turn your attention to a man whose contributions to meteorology are celebrated. How many degrees did he earn during his time at a renowned educational institution?\n\n9. Finally, to complete your quest, resolve the expression formed by the parks near the river from clue 4 and the population from clue 6: compute the absolute difference between 2 and the population, then take that result modulo 10. What single digit do you obtain?",
